nsidering DSAParams serialization**\\n\\nI'm exploring how to create a normal key and set `dsaSpec`. I might not need the variable `x` after all. I should consider adding `DSAParamsWithTrackedValues`. It seems I don’t have to utilize full serialization. I’m wondering if private field access might require some metadata in native code. It looks like `MethodHandles.privateLookupIn` and `findVarHandle` could locate private fields if they’re included. I noticed the tests passed with private methods—probably because the call site was at build time.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Editing file modifications**\\n\\nI need to focus on using method handles only at build time during static initialization. It seems to have worked, which is great! Now, I’ll need to modify the file to use real streams instead of recorded ones. That change should improve functionality, so let’s get started on editing it. I'm curious about how these modifications will affect the overall performance!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_kNFwAYoDhxCoTRUm8B3Eo5WN|fc_085e825c48b4c65f0169fbc2bbf550819d89a286d196023123", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk18on/BCDSAPrivateKeyTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 693, "output": 1126, "cacheRead": 40960, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42779, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778107049347, "responseId": "resp_085e825c48b4c65f0169fbc2aa1a98819d9fc3ce2f090eb505"}}
